headline: BYD, Nvidia, Monday.com: 3 Stocks In Focus
summary: BYD (1211.HK, BYDDY) could ship more cars in 2024 than Ford (F) after the Chinese automaker sold more than 500,000 vehicles in October. The EV maker's quarterly revenue surpassed Tesla's (TSLA) in its latest earnings report. Nvidia (NVDA) is Piper Sandler's large-cap pick ahead of the chipmaker's third quarter earnings call on November 20, which could give more detail on the company's position in the artificial intelligence (AI) chip market. Monday.com (MNDY) shares are sinking despite the company reporting third quarter earnings and seeing revenue grow 33% year-over-year. To watch more expert insights and analysis on the latest market action, check out more Morning Brief here. This post was written by Naomi Buchanan.
